## Phase III — Agentic Trust Framework
**Status: Not Started | Q3–Q4 2025**

The inflection point. When AI stops being supervised and starts being autonomous.

Enterprises deploying LLM agents, multi-agent orchestration pipelines, and autonomous decision systems cannot govern them with human-review workflows designed for static models. A model that acts is fundamentally different from a model that predicts. Phase II governance controls are necessary but insufficient for agentic systems.

**Industry Forcing Function:** EU AI Act Article 14 mandates human oversight of high-risk AI systems. NIST AI RMF Govern function requires continuous monitoring of autonomous system behavior. Neither can be satisfied with dashboard visibility alone — they require infrastructure-layer policy enforcement at execution time.

| Item | Description | Status | Dependencies |
|---|---|---|---|
| Twin Agent Consensus Layer | Dual-agent validation before autonomous action execution — no single agent acts unilaterally | Not Started | Phase II model registry |
| Lifeguard Rescue Patterns | Automatic circuit breakers: detect agent drift, hallucination loops, and policy violations mid-execution | Not Started | Policy engine + telemetry |
| Continuous Attestation | Real-time cryptographic proof that agent behavior matches declared policy at execution time | Not Started | Immutable audit log + signing infrastructure |
| Agentic Risk Scoring | Dynamic risk tier recalculation as agent behavior evolves — static model cards are insufficient | Not Started | Phase II scoring algorithm |
| Human-in-the-Loop Escalation | Threshold-triggered escalation with full context handoff to human oversight | Not Started | RBAC + notification layer |
| CSA STAR for AI Alignment | Map all Phase III controls to CSA STAR for AI certification framework | Not Started | CSA working group deliverables |

**Phase III Exit Criteria:**
- Any autonomous agent deployment has cryptographic audit trail
- No agent executes high-risk actions without real-time attestation
- STAR for AI certification pathway fully documented and submitted

