## Phase IV — Quantum-Safe Governance Operations
**Status: Not Started | 2026+**

The endpoint. Where this platform was always going.

Classical cryptographic infrastructure underpinning AI governance — audit logs, attestation chains, policy signing, identity verification — is vulnerable to Harvest Now, Decrypt Later attacks already in progress by nation-state actors. Regulated industries operating AI at scale have a hard compliance deadline: post-quantum migration must begin before cryptographically relevant quantum computers arrive, not after.

Phase IV is not a feature addition to Phase II. It is the reason the architecture was designed the way it was from the beginning.

**Industry Forcing Function:** NIST finalized PQC standards in 2024 (CRYSTALS-Kyber, CRYSTALS-Dilithium, SPHINCS+). NSA CNSA 2.0 mandates quantum-resistant algorithms for national security systems by 2030. DoD Zero Trust Architecture Strategy requires continuous verification that classical cryptography cannot sustain. This is not speculative — it is a compliance deadline with a known horizon.

| Item | Description | Status | Dependencies |
|---|---|---|---|
| K8sX-QEG Integration | Post-quantum Kubernetes security fabric as compute substrate for all governance operations | Not Started | Phase III attestation layer |
| Q-OPA Policy Engine | Quantum-extended OPA/Rego enforcement at OSI Layer 3 — cryptographically tamper-proof policy decisions | Not Started | K8sX-QEG |
| PQC Audit Chain | CRYSTALS-Kyber / CRYSTALS-Dilithium signed audit logs — immutable records that survive quantum decryption | Not Started | Phase II audit log architecture |
| AQ-KRAE | Autonomous Quantum Key Rotation and Attestation Engine — continuous key lifecycle without human intervention | Not Started | Q-OPA + K8sX-QEG |
| QFEN Integration | Quantum Federated Edge Network — extends governance controls to edge deployments outside central cloud | Not Started | Phase III agentic controls |
| cATO Quantum Extension | Extend continuous ATO workflow to include PQC compliance gates — compress quantum migration from years to weeks | Not Started | Phase IV policy engine |
| DoD / FedRAMP PQC Alignment | Map all Phase IV controls to NIST SP 800-208, CNSA 2.0, and DoD Zero Trust Architecture requirements | Not Started | CSA + DoD engagement |

**Phase IV Exit Criteria:**
- All governance cryptography is NIST PQC standard compliant
- Audit chain cryptographically survives quantum decryption attempts
- cATO quantum migration timeline documented and validated against FedRAMP High baseline
- DoD alignment pathway established through CSA standards contribution

